---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import FAQSection from '../components/FAQSection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Brand Mark | Your Logo, Hand-Painted. $500. | Untitled Mixed Media"
  description="Most business signs look like they came from a catalog. The Brand Mark is your logo, hand-painted on your wall or on wood in one day. Three shapes. $500 for the first 12 businesses in Richmond, VA."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="pt-24 pb-16">

    <!-- Section 1: Hero -->
    <div class="px-6 lg:px-12 max-w-4xl mb-24">
      <Breadcrumb items={[
        { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
        { label: 'Brand Mark' },
      ]} />

      <p class="font-mono text-smoke-gray uppercase mb-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);">
        The Brand Mark
      </p>

      <h1 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-6" data-animate>
        Your logo. Hand-painted. $500.
      </h1>

      <p
        class="font-body text-shadow-gray max-w-xl mb-10"
        style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
        data-animate
        data-animate-delay="1"
      >
        A vinyl decal tells your customers you ordered your sign from a catalog. A Brand Mark tells them you hired a craftsperson. One day. Done.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4" data-animate data-animate-delay="2">
        <a
          href="/contact?type=brand-mark"
          class="font-sans inline-block bg-titanium-white text-bone-black px-8 py-3.5 text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.15em] uppercase hover:bg-light-ash transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          Send Your Logo File
        </a>
        <a
          href="#how-it-works"
          class="font-sans inline-block border border-titanium-white text-titanium-white px-8 py-3.5 text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.15em] uppercase hover:bg-titanium-white hover:text-bone-black transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          See How It Works <span aria-hidden="true">&darr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 2: What You Get -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-12 max-w-4xl mb-24">
      <p class="font-mono text-smoke-gray uppercase mb-6" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);" data-animate="fade">
        What You Get
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-6" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-3xl);" data-animate="fade">
        Your logo, hand-painted on your wall or on a wood panel.
      </h2>

      <div class="font-body text-shadow-gray max-w-2xl space-y-4 mb-12" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
        <p>Up to 16 square feet. Single color of your choice. Clean edges. Consistent coverage. No shortcuts.</p>
        <p>The panel comes with a weathered ghost-sign finish: your logo looks like it's been on your wall for decades. Want it clean and modern instead? Just ask.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Three Shapes -->
      <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-8" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xl);" data-animate="fade">
        Three Shapes
      </h3>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
        <div class="border border-slate-gray p-6 text-center">
          <div class="aspect-square w-20 mx-auto mb-4 border border-smoke-gray flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs);">4' &times; 4'</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base);">Square</h4>
          <p class="font-body text-smoke-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-sm);">16 sq ft. Great for square logos, circular logos, and stacked designs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-slate-gray p-6 text-center">
          <div class="aspect-[5/3] w-24 mx-auto mb-4 border border-smoke-gray flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs);">3' &times; 5'</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base);">Rectangle</h4>
          <p class="font-body text-smoke-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-sm);">15 sq ft. Great for most horizontal logos and logo-plus-tagline combos.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-slate-gray p-6 text-center">
          <div class="aspect-[4/1] w-32 mx-auto mb-4 border border-smoke-gray flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs);">2' &times; 8'</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base);">Banner</h4>
          <p class="font-body text-smoke-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-sm);">16 sq ft. Great for single-word names and long wordmarks. Perfect above a bar or along a wall.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="font-body text-smoke-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-sm);">
        Not sure which shape fits your logo? Send it over. I'll tell you which one works best.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: The Real Cost of Vinyl -->
    <section class="bg-midnight-graphite border-y border-slate-gray py-24 lg:py-32 px-6 lg:px-12 mb-24">
      <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-6" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-3xl);" data-animate="fade">
          The math most sign shops don't want you to see.
        </h2>

        <div class="font-body text-shadow-gray max-w-2xl space-y-4 mb-12" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
          <p>A vinyl sign costs $200 and lasts 3 years. It peels, fades, and bubbles. Replace it three times over 12 years: that's $600+ on signage that looks worse every year.</p>
          <p>A Brand Mark costs $500 and lasts 20+ years. It ages with character. It gets better over time.</p>
          <p>Over 12 years, vinyl costs more and looks cheaper. Hand-painted costs less and looks more valuable every day.</p>
        </div>

        <a
          href="/journal/hand-painted-vs-vinyl"
          class="font-sans inline-block border border-slate-gray text-smoke-gray px-8 py-3.5 text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.15em] uppercase hover:border-titanium-white hover:text-titanium-white transition-colors duration-200"
          data-animate="fade"
          data-animate-delay="2"
        >
          Download: Hand-Painted vs. Vinyl &mdash; The Real Cost Over 12 Years (PDF)
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Everything Included (Value Stack) -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-12 max-w-4xl mb-24">
      <p class="font-mono text-smoke-gray uppercase mb-6" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);" data-animate="fade">
        Everything Included
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-12" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-3xl);" data-animate="fade">
        $1,000+ in value. $500 for the first 12 businesses.
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-10" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-slate-gray pl-8">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg);">The Opening Day Reel</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray shrink-0 ml-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs);">$150 value</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            Full process time-lapse of the painting from blank surface to finished work. Shot during the session, delivered to your phone the same day. Post it to Instagram, TikTok, your Google listing. It's yours.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-slate-gray pl-8">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg);">The GBP Photo Set</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray shrink-0 ml-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs);">$100 value</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            Professional before-and-after photos, cropped and sized for Instagram, Facebook, and Google Business Profile. Ready to post the same day.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-slate-gray pl-8">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg);">The Forever Kit</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray shrink-0 ml-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs);">$75 value</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            A jar of the exact paint used on your Brand Mark, plus a detail brush. Scuffs happen. You fix them in 30 seconds.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-slate-gray pl-8">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg);">The Done-For-You Install</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray shrink-0 ml-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs);">$75 value</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray mb-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            <span class="font-heading text-titanium-white">Panel format:</span> French cleat or appropriate hardware for your wall type, installed before I leave. You don't go to the hardware store. You don't Google "how to hang a heavy sign." It's on the wall before I walk out the door.
          </p>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            <span class="font-heading text-titanium-white">Wall format &mdash; The Care Plan:</span> A one-page guide covering how to clean the surface, what products to avoid, and when to schedule a refresh. Written for your specific wall material and paint type.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-slate-gray pl-8">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg);">$100 Credit Toward Your Next Project</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray shrink-0 ml-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs);">$100 value</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            Good toward any future Untitled Mixed Media project: a full custom sign, a mural, a restoration, a second Brand Mark. When you're ready for more, you're already $100 ahead.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 5: Pricing Block -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-12 max-w-4xl mb-24">
      <div class="border border-slate-gray p-8 lg:p-12" data-animate="fade">
        <p
          class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-4"
          style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-5xl); line-height: var(--leading-solid);"
        >
          $500
        </p>
        <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray mb-8" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
          Launch price for the first 12 businesses. Then the price goes up.
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-10 font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base);">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-titanium-white mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">&check;</span>
            Your logo, hand-painted (wall or panel, up to 16 sq ft)
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-titanium-white mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">&check;</span>
            The Opening Day Reel (process time-lapse video)
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-titanium-white mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">&check;</span>
            The GBP Photo Set (before-and-after photos)
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-titanium-white mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">&check;</span>
            The Forever Kit (matched paint + detail brush)
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-titanium-white mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">&check;</span>
            The Done-For-You Install or The Care Plan
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-titanium-white mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">&check;</span>
            $100 credit toward your next project
          </li>
        </ul>

        <a
          href="/contact?type=brand-mark"
          class="font-sans inline-block bg-titanium-white text-bone-black px-8 py-3.5 text-sm font-medium tracking-[0.15em] uppercase hover:bg-light-ash transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          Send Your Logo File
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 6: The Guarantee -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-12 max-w-4xl mb-24">
      <p class="font-mono text-smoke-gray uppercase mb-6" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);" data-animate="fade">
        The Guarantee
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-8" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-3xl);" data-animate="fade">
        No risk. No exceptions.
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg);">Panel format</h3>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            If you look at the finished panel and you're not happy, I take it home with me. You owe nothing. You never see a bill.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg);">Wall format</h3>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            If any line isn't clean, any coverage isn't consistent, or the finished work doesn't match your logo file, I keep working until it does. If you're not happy, I paint over it myself. No charge.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 7: How It Works -->
    <section id="how-it-works" class="bg-midnight-graphite border-y border-slate-gray py-24 lg:py-32 px-6 lg:px-12 mb-24">
      <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <p class="font-mono text-smoke-gray uppercase mb-12" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);" data-animate="fade">
          How It Works
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-12">
          <div data-animate="fade">
            <span class="font-heading text-slate-gray block mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-4xl); line-height: var(--leading-solid);" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg);">Send your logo file and pick your format.</h3>
            <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
              Wall or wood panel. I'll confirm everything works and lock in your date.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
            <span class="font-heading text-slate-gray block mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-4xl); line-height: var(--leading-solid);" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg);">Pay $250 to reserve your spot.</h3>
            <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
              Your date is held. I show up with everything needed. No supplies for you to buy. No prep for you to do.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="2">
            <span class="font-heading text-slate-gray block mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-4xl); line-height: var(--leading-solid);" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-2" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg);">Pay the balance when you approve it.</h3>
            <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
              The remaining $250 is due only after you've seen the finished work and signed off. Then I hand you your time-lapse, your photos, your touch-up kit, and your $100 project credit.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 8: Why the Wood Panel? -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-12 max-w-4xl mb-24">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-6" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-3xl);" data-animate="fade">
        Can't paint your walls? The panel solves that.
      </h2>

      <div class="font-body text-shadow-gray max-w-2xl space-y-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
        <p>Some businesses can't paint their walls. Your landlord won't allow it. Your lease restricts alterations. Your walls are exposed brick and you don't want to cover them. You're in a pop-up space. You want something you can take with you when you grow into a bigger spot.</p>
        <p>The wood panel fixes all of it. It hangs like a frame. It comes down without a mark. And it goes wherever you go: behind the bar today, at the farmers market Saturday, on a different wall next year.</p>
        <p>The ghost-sign weathered finish is the real difference. A clean vinyl sign says "we just ordered this." A Brand Mark says "we've been here. This place has character."</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 9: Who This Is For -->
    <section class="px-6 lg:px-12 max-w-4xl mb-24">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div data-animate="fade">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xl);">Who this is for</h3>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            Small businesses and storefronts in Richmond, Virginia who want their name on their wall without a six-month timeline or a $5,000 quote. Breweries, barbershops, coffee shops, studios, gyms, boutiques, restaurants, bakeries, tattoo shops, coworking spaces. If you have a logo and a wall (or want a panel), this is for you.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xl);">Who this is NOT for</h3>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            If you want a full custom mural, a multi-color design, gold leaf lettering, or something larger than 16 square feet, that's a different conversation. <a href="/contact" class="text-titanium-white underline hover:no-underline">Reach out</a> and we'll scope a custom project. (That's how you know this offer is real: I'm telling you exactly where it ends.)
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 10: Neighborhood Availability -->
    <section class="bg-midnight-graphite border-y border-slate-gray py-24 lg:py-32 px-6 lg:px-12 mb-24">
      <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-6" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-3xl);" data-animate="fade">
          The Brand Mark is available by neighborhood.
        </h2>

        <div class="font-body text-shadow-gray max-w-2xl space-y-4 mb-10" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
          <p>I paint 3 Brand Marks per neighborhood, then move to the next. Each one takes a full day, and I reserve the rest of my week for larger mural and sign projects. When the 3 spots in your neighborhood are filled, the next round is a few months out.</p>
          <p>The $500 price is the launch price for the first 12 businesses. After that, the price increases to reflect demand.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Dynamic availability — update these values manually as Brand Marks are completed -->
        <div class="border border-slate-gray p-8 mb-8 space-y-3" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="2">
          <p class="font-body text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base);">
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray uppercase mr-3" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);">Currently painting in:</span> Scott's Addition
          </p>
          <p class="font-body text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base);">
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray uppercase mr-3" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);">Spots remaining:</span> 3 of 3
          </p>
          <p class="font-body text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base);">
            <span class="font-mono text-smoke-gray uppercase mr-3" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);">Brand Marks completed:</span> 0 of 12 at launch price
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
          If your neighborhood isn't open yet, <a href="/contact?type=brand-mark" class="text-titanium-white underline hover:no-underline">join the waitlist</a>. You'll get first priority when I come to your area.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 11: FAQ -->
    <FAQSection heading="Questions people ask" items={[
      { question: "I don't have a good logo file.", answer: "Send me whatever you have. A photo of your old sign, a screenshot from your website, even a business card. I can work with almost anything." },
      { question: 'My wall is in bad shape.', answer: "That's what the panel format is for. I paint on wood in my studio and hang it on your wall. Bad surfaces aren't a problem." },
      { question: 'What if I move?', answer: "Panel: take it with you. It's yours. Wall: this is one of the reasons the panel format exists. If there's a chance you'll move, the panel is the smarter choice." },
      { question: 'Can I pick the color?', answer: "Yes. One color of your choice. If you want full multi-color, that's a custom sign project at a different price." },
      { question: 'How long does it take?', answer: 'One day. I paint it, you see it, you approve it, done.' },
      { question: 'What happens when it gets dirty or scratched?', answer: 'You get The Forever Kit: a jar of the exact paint I used, plus a detail brush. Scuffs and nicks happen. You fix them yourself in 30 seconds.' },
      { question: 'Do I need to be there?', answer: 'Wall format: yes, someone needs to let me in. Panel format: no. I paint it in my studio and deliver it.' },
      { question: 'What if I want more work later?', answer: "You already have a $100 credit toward any future Untitled Mixed Media project. When you're ready for a mural, a custom sign, or a second Brand Mark, you're $100 ahead." },
    ]} />

    <!-- Section 12: Closing CTA -->
    <section class="border-t border-slate-gray py-24 lg:py-32 px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center" data-animate="fade">
        <h2
          class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-6"
